stacks

Class StackList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stacks.LinkedList<E>
      • stacks.StackList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements held in this stack
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>

    public class StackList<E>
extends LinkedList<E>
    Represents a last-in-first-out (LIFO) stack of objects. It extends LinkedList with push, pop, peek, isEmpty, size and clear operations to allow the linked list to be treated as a stack. When a stack is created it has no items. In a stack data structure insertion and deletion is always at the top of the stack (LIFO). A special node is designated as top and keeps track of the top of the stack.
    Author:
    anuva
